          "criteria": "Session creation delegates to adapter. Prompt delivery delegates to adapter instead of returning 409. HP-1 and HP-6 pass.",
          "test_file": "tests/acceptance/sandbox-session-lifecycle.test.ts",
          "scenario_name": "HP-1, HP-6"
        },
        {
          "id": "02-04",
          "name": "Route wiring and event bridge to SSE",
          "criteria": "Adapter injected via route wiring. Event bridge connected to SSE delivery. Old SDK event translation removed. HP-2 and HP-3 pass.",
          "test_file": "tests/acceptance/sandbox-session-lifecycle.test.ts",
          "scenario_name": "HP-2, HP-3"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "03",
      "name": "Integration and Walking Skeleton",
      "steps": [
        {
          "id": "03-01",
          "name": "Walking skeleton E2E acceptance test",
          "criteria": "WS-1 passes: spawn, prompt, SSE events, SurrealDB record verified. Error paths EP-1, EP-2, EP-5 pass.",
          "test_file": "tests/acceptance/sandbox-session-lifecycle.test.ts",
          "scenario_name": "WS-1, EP-1, EP-2, EP-5"
        },
        {
          "id": "03-02",
          "name": "Multi-turn, persistence, remaining tests",
          "criteria": "WS-2, WS-3, HP-4 pass. Error paths EP-3, EP-4, EP-6, EP-7 pass. Edge cases EC-1, EC-2 pass.",
          "test_file": "tests/acceptance/sandbox-session-lifecycle.test.ts",
          "scenario_name": "WS-2, WS-3, HP-4, EP-3, EP-4, EP-6, EP-7, EC-1, EC-2"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "04",
      "name": "R2: Proxy Token with Intent Binding + Adapter Env Wiring",
      "steps": [
        {
          "id": "04-01",
          "name": "Schema migration: add intent + session fields to proxy_token",
          "criteria": "Migration adds option<record<intent>> intent field and option<record<agent_session>> session field to proxy_token table. resolveProxyAuth returns intentId and sessionId when present. ProxyAuthResult type extended. Unit tests verify round-trip: token with intent+session resolves correctly. Token without intent (legacy CLI tokens) still resolves.",
          "test_file": "tests/unit/proxy/proxy-auth.test.ts",
          "scenario_name": "PA-10, PA-11, PA-12, PA-13"
        },
        {
          "id": "04-02",
          "name": "Extend SessionCreateRequest with env record",
          "criteria": "SessionCreateRequest type extended with optional env: Record<string, string>. Mock adapter captures env for assertion. createSessionViaAdapter passes env to adapter.createSession. Unit tests verify env passthrough and env omission when undefined.",
          "test_file": "tests/unit/orchestrator/sandbox-adapter.test.ts",
          "scenario_name": "UA-7, UA-8"
        },
        {
          "id": "04-03",
          "name": "Wire proxy token issuance into adapter spawn path",
          "criteria": "Adapter spawn path in routes.ts creates initial composite intent with BrainAction entries for expected tool chain (derived from task context). Runs intent through policy gate. Issues proxy token linked to authorized intent and session via new fields. Passes ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL (brainBaseUrl/proxy/llm/anthropic) and X-Brain-Auth (raw proxy token) as env to adapter. Acceptance test: proxy_token record has intent + session fields. Acceptance test: session env includes proxy URL + auth header.",
          "test_file": "tests/acceptance/sandbox-session-governance.test.ts",
          "scenario_name": "PW-1, PW-2, PW-3"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "05",
      "name": "R2: Dynamic Per-Agent MCP Endpoint",
      "steps": [
        {
          "id": "05-01",
          "name": "Agent MCP endpoint: tools/list with grant filtering",
          "criteria": "New route GET /mcp/agent/:sessionId/tools/list. Auth via X-Brain-Auth (resolveProxyAuth → identity + session). Resolves effective toolset: can_use grants filtered to tools covered by any authorized intent linked to session via gates edges. Returns MCP JSON-RPC tool list. Unit tests: grant filtering respects intent scope, invalid token 401, no grants returns empty list.",
          "test_file": "tests/unit/mcp/agent-mcp-route.test.ts",
          "scenario_name": "AM-1, AM-2, AM-3"
        },
        {
          "id": "05-02",
          "name": "Agent MCP endpoint: tools/call with intent check + trace",
          "criteria": "New route POST /mcp/agent/:sessionId/tools/call. Resolves session from proxy token. Queries all intents linked via gates edges. Checks requested tool+params against union of authorization_details across all session intents. If covered: forward to upstream MCP via executeAllToolCalls, create trace record. If not covered: return 403 with escalation hint. Unit tests: covered tool succeeds, uncovered tool 403, trace created on success.",
          "test_file": "tests/unit/mcp/agent-mcp-route.test.ts",
          "scenario_name": "AM-4, AM-5, AM-6"
        },
        {
          "id": "05-03",
          "name": "Wire MCP endpoint URL into session spawn env",
          "criteria": "After proxy token issued, add BRAIN_MCP_URL (brainBaseUrl/mcp/agent/{sessionId}) to adapter env alongside ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL. Same X-Brain-Auth token authenticates both planes. Unit test verifies env includes both URLs with matching token.",
          "test_file": "tests/unit/orchestrator/session-lifecycle.test.ts",
          "scenario_name": "SL-10, SL-11"
        },
        {
          "id": "05-04",
          "name": "Acceptance test: MCP endpoint serves filtered tools and checks intent scope",
          "criteria": "AM-7: Grant 3 tools via can_use, authorize 2 via intent, tools/list returns only the 2 that are both granted AND intent-authorized. AM-8: tools/call for granted-but-not-intent-authorized tool returns 403. AM-9: tools/call for fully authorized tool returns result and creates trace. AM-10: After escalation adds new intent via gates, previously blocked tool now succeeds.",
          "test_file": "tests/acceptance/sandbox-session-governance.test.ts",
          "scenario_name": "AM-7, AM-8, AM-9, AM-10"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "06",
      "name": "R2: Permission Handler with Intent Escalation",
      "steps": [
        {
          "id": "06-01",
          "name": "Permission handler: escalation creates new intents linked via gates",
          "criteria": "New module permission-handler.ts. When sandbox agent requests permission for an action not covered by existing session intents: (1) creates new intent with BrainAction for the requested action, (2) runs through policy gate, (3) if auto-approved: creates gates edge to session, responds approved, (4) if requires human review: emits SSE permission_request event, waits for response, (5) on human approve: authorizes intent + creates gates edge, responds approved, (6) on human reject or 60s timeout: responds denied. Unit tests: auto-approve path, human approval path, timeout auto-reject, gates edge created on approval.",
          "test_file": "tests/unit/orchestrator/permission-handler.test.ts",
          "scenario_name": "PH-1, PH-2, PH-3, PH-4, PH-5"
        },
        {
          "id": "06-02",
          "name": "E2E governance acceptance test",
          "criteria": "GOV-1: Spawn session, verify proxy URL + MCP URL in env, tools/list returns intent-scoped tools. GOV-2: proxy_token has intent + session fields linking to authorized intent and agent_session. GOV-3: Tool call outside intent scope triggers permission request via SSE. GOV-4: After human approval, new intent linked via gates, previously blocked tool now works. GOV-5: Full provenance chain: initial intent → gates → session, escalation intent → gates → session, proxy_token → initial intent.",
          "test_file": "tests/acceptance/sandbox-session-governance.test.ts",
          "scenario_name": "GOV-1, GOV-2, GOV-3, GOV-4, GOV-5"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "implementation_scope": {
    "source_directories": [
      "app/src/server/orchestrator/",
      "app/src/server/mcp/",
      "app/src/server/proxy/",
      "app/src/shared/",
      "schema/migrations/"
    ],
    "test_directories": [
      "tests/unit/orchestrator/",
      "tests/unit/mcp/",
      "tests/acceptance/"
    ],
    "excluded_patterns": [
      "node_modules/**",
      "dist/**",
      "*.d.ts"
    ]
  },
  "validation": {
    "status": "approved",
    "reviewer": "nw-solution-architect-reviewer",
    "approved_at": "2026-03-25T06:45:00Z"
  }
}

